definition.value: A dicarboxylic acid consisting of succinic acid carrying a 3-methylbenzyl group at position 2.

A diastereoisomeric mixture containing containing 80-100% of the (4R,5S)-isomer and 0-20% of (4R,5R)-,(4S,5R)-, and (4S,5S)-isomers. It is a broad-spectrum insecticide and acaricide developed by Syngenta Crop Protection that is active against several pest species including lepidopteran, hemipteran, and dipteran pest species.

A member of the class of isoxazoles that is 4,5-dihydro-1,2-oxazole substituted by 4-[(2-ethyl-3-oxo-1,2-oxazolidin-4-yl)carbamoyl]-3-methylphenyl, trifluoromethyl, and 3,5-dichloro-4-fluorophenyl groups at positions 3, 5, and 5, respectively.
A dicarboxylic acid dianion resulting from the deprotonation of the two carboxy groups of 3-hydroxyglutaric acid; major species at pH 7.3.
A HETE that is icosa-5,8,10,14-tetraenoic acid substituted by a hydroxy group at position 12. It is a metabolite of arachidonic acid.
An aryl sulfate that is 2,4-xylenol in which the phenolic hydrogen has been replaced by a sulfo group.
A member of the class of phenols that phenol substituted by methyl groups at positions 2 and 5.
An aryl sulfate that is 2,5-xylenol in which the phenolic hydrogen has been replaced by a sulfo group.
A dicarboxylic acid dianion resulting from the deprotonation of the two carboxy groups of 2,2-dimethylsuccinic acid; major species at pH 7.3.
A dicarboxylic acid dianion resulting from the deprotonation of the two carboxy groups of  2,3-dimethylsuccinic acid ; major species at pH 7.3.

An N-alkylpyrrolidine that is pyrrolidine substituted by methyl, oxo, (2-fluorophenyl)aminocarbonyl, and 3-(trifluoromethyl)phenyl groups at positions 1, 2, 3, and 4, respectively. It is a herbicide developed by FMC Corporation for the control of grass weeds in rice, as well as key broadleaf weeds and sedges.
A cyclic hexapeptide with the amino acid sequence cyclo-(D-Ala-L-Leu-D-allo-Thr-L-Pro-D-Leu-L-Leu). Fusahexin is a secondary metabolite produced by the plant pathogenic fungus Fusarium graminearum.
Major microspecies at pH 7.3
A N-[2-(4-bromocinnamylamino)ethyl]isoquinoline-5-sulfonamide in which the double bond adopts a trans-configuration.
The prenylated form of butyrolactone II; major microspecies at pH 7.3
An organic anionic group obtained by deprotonation of the diphosphate OH groups of N(tele)-(ADP-D-ribosyl)-L-histidyl residue; major microspeciess at pH 7.3.
A 4-methylidene-2-octyl-5-oxotetrahydrofuran-3-carboxylic acid that has 2R,3S-configuration.
A 4-methylidene-2-octyl-5-oxotetrahydrofuran-3-carboxylic acid that has 2S,3R-configuration.
A tetrahydrofuranone that is tetrahydrofuran substituted by octyl, carboxy, methylidene, and oxo groups at positions 2, 3, 4 and 5, respectively.

A branched amino hexasaccharide that is beta-D-Manp-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->4)-D-GlcpNAc in which the hydroxy groups at positions 2 and 3 of the mannosyl residue have been glycosylated by beta-D-xylopyranosyl and alpha-D-mannopyranosyl residues respectively, while the GlcNAc residue at the reducing end carries also an alpha-L-fucosyl residue attached via a (1->3)-linkage.
